Let $f$ be twice differentiable on $(a,b)$.
    - If $f''(x) > 0$ on $(a,b)$,then $f$ is convex on $(a,b)$
    - If $f''(x) < 0$ on $(a,b)$ then $f$ is concave on $(a,b)$
    
